== Installation ==
To use this adapter, you must first install OKO-Control Server software which can be downloaded [https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/29705430/OCS/OKO-Control%20Server%202.8.0.zip here].
The installation is straightforward, default settings can be used.

== Configuration ==

# Open the Hardware Configuration Wizard from the Tools menu.
# Select desired configuration (new or existing) and  press the bottom-right Next button.
# Add OKO Control Server device to the current configuration double-clicking on it or clicking the Add button when selected.
# Add one or more Okolab devices.
{{Note|Okolab devices can be found in the Okolab node if Available Devices list is ordered by vendor or Generic Device node if list is ordered by type.}}

== Usage ==
=== Properties ===

For every Device added to the Configuration, some managed properties are shown in the Device/Property Browser list (Tools menu). Okolab devices properties are listed only if the Show other devices checkbox is enabled.
Any writeable property is listed as a white row and can be changed clicking on it and clicking enter (eg. H301-T Unit-BL Set Point).

=== Live mode ===

If live is enabled, values acquired from Okolab devices are automatically refreshed in the Metadata tab.

=== Logging ===

To log data from Okolab devices, an experiment must be started (Tools > Multi-Dimensional Acquisition). Data are logged in the metadata.txt file if Separate images files is selected or in the same image file is Image stack file is selected.

